The paper proposes a new graph-based coding framework for image compression, which involves designing an optimized graph and using a novel graph estimation algorithm. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sparsity and Fourier transforms, which are common in Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed technique to natural image and piecewise smooth image coding, which could fall under the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
